# Data & fixtures (BuildY)

## Data layers

1. **`internal/fixtures/site/*.json`** — app chrome copy and navigation (`SiteLocale`, `LoadSiteLocale`).
2. **`internal/fixtures/screens/*.json`** — screen-specific view copy (`LoadHomeScreen`, `LoadSampleScreen`, ...).
3. **`internal/fixtures/cms/*.json`** — AppCMS-compatible `codex.v1` seed bundles.
4. **Provider layer** (`internal/site`) — resolves locale and builds **`views.LayoutData`** / page structs with **already-translated** strings.

## Rules

- User-visible runtime copy lives in **`site/*.json`** and **`screens/*.json`** — not hard-coded in `.templ`.
- Extend typed fixture structs + every supported locale file when adding new UI strings (theme labels, nav labels, page copy).
- Keep AppCMS seed content in **`cms/*.json`** and validate it against AppCMS codex schemas.
- **`internal/views`** and **`internal/ui/components`** take props only; no fixture imports in templ.
- Keep **accessible names** (aria labels, button titles) in fixtures when used as `aria-label`.

## Locale switching

- Header control: **`toggles.LanguageSwitch`** built in `site/feature.go` via **`locale.BuildLangHref`**.
- Framework cookie/query strategy is configured in `cmd/server/main.go` (`WithLocales`).

See **`buildy-atomic-ui8px.mdc`** for presentation boundaries.
